summary: picture this: It’s a few months after Endgame comes out. You’re in a shawarma restaurant minding your own business, eating lunch...
body: picture this: It’s a few months after Endgame comes out. You’re in a shawarma restaurant minding your own business, eating lunch (likely during non-regular lunch hours and enjoying the quiet), when someone in an Avengers costume, whoever survives, walks inside the door, stands in front of an unoccupied table, and starts to sing “Empty Chairs at Empty Tables” to an empty table.
